  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2006-11-16",
    "date": "2007-02-06T19:21:48Z",
    "text": "Satellite Consumer Protection Act of 2006 - Grants a satellite carrier under an injunction for certain secondary transmission violations a statutory license to provide distant network stations in specified local markets under prescribed conditions. Requires a satellite carrier as a condition of license use to deposit escrow funds with the Copyright Office. Imposes monetary penalties for license violations.\n\nTerminates such license authority after February 17, 2009."
  },
